# Versioned documentation archives (default)

Any package that owns a `/packages/<id>/` docs section **must** have versioned documentation archives enabled. This is required by default for current and new packages — not opt-in.

When adding a new package docs section:

1. Register in `DOC_VERSIONED_PACKAGES` (`scripts/lib/doc-versioning.mjs`)
2. Create `apps/docs/doc-versions/<id>.json` with `archivePolicy: "minor"` and `archives: []`
3. Wire versions meta into VitePress config, sidebar map, `DocsVersionSwitcher`, and `ArchivedDocsBanner`
4. Gitignore `apps/docs/docs/packages/<id>/v*/` and `.vitepress/<id>-versions.ts`
5. Bootstrap on first publish: `pnpm docs:archive -- --package <id> --bootstrap`

Policy: `engineering/014-versioning-policy.md`. Checklist: `engineering/017-package-doc-learning-path.md`.
